Lean 4 is an array-based sorting algorithm which uses the timsort algorithm. Timsort works by comparing two elements and placing them in an order based on their relationship. In the case of Lean 4, the elements are compared to the pivot element and placed in order from lower to higher values. This is repeated recursively until the array is sorted. The code for Lean 4 is as follows: 

def lean4(arr, n, pivot): 
    # divide the array into two halves 
    left = [i for i in arr] 
    right = [i for i in arr] 
    # loop through the left array and find the pivot 
    for i in range(len(left)): 
        if left[i] < pivot: 
            right.append(left[i]) 
    # loop through the right array and insert the pivot 
    for i in range(len(right)): 
        if right[i] > pivot: 
            left.insert(i, right[i]) 
    # repeat until the array is sorted 
    while left and right: 
        i = left.index(min(left)) 
        left.remove(min(left)) 
        right.remove(right.pop()) 
    return left + right

